Package comp3110.mechanismsDomain

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    TimerConstants
    The TimerConstants interface provides handy constants for specifying delays.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ActiveClass
    All classes in an xtUML domain that have dynamic behaviour are implemented as java classes which extend the ActiveClass class.
    Application
    All applications are implemented as classes which extend the Application class.
    ApplicationEventQueue
    All events generated in xtUML models are put on to the ApplicationEventQueue for later asynschronous processing.
    Domain
    Each executable domain in an application is implemented as a java class which extends the Domain class.
    EventInstance
    All events generated during the execution of an application are implemented as instances of the EventInstance Java class.
    EventQueue
    This class implements a simple queue used by the ApplicationEventQueue
    Messages
    The Messages class provides standardised formatting for error and debug messages
    State
    Each state in an xtUML State Model is implemented as a class which extends the State class.
    Timer
    The Timer class is used to implement the timed event generation actions available in the ApplicationEventQueue class.
    Transition
    All transitions between states in an xtUML state model are implemented as instances of the Transition class.
